&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse - Band 5 - Cancer Services&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are currently recruiting a Registered Nurse to work within Cancer services, this post will support the increasing demand on the local service and is in line with the national trend of increased patient activity and available therapy. The candidate will be expected to provide a high standard of care, support patient who receive anticancer and supportive treatments within Torbay &amp; South Devon NHS Foundation Trust.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The successful candidate will have the opportunity to develop their skills specifically caring for patient with a cancer diagnosis and support patients and their carers on all aspects of their care, be they newly diagnosed or being treated with palliative intent.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;They will be required to work flexibly on the inpatient ward and/or day unit. This will involve a range of shift patterns which will include long days, weekends and rotation to night duty.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The candidate may have post registration experience within this field, but this is not essential as education and support will be available, the candidate should have clear communication skills to be able to articulate clearly and be educated or working towards degree level. However, we would consider experienced medical nurses looking for experience within Oncology/Haematology.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
